{
  "stem": "3022.1",
  "chunk_idx": 9,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 6.2,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "I remember walking on the street with my mother, a Friday afternoon, and being jostled by a Polish-- drunken Polish soldier and then accused for having called him a Polish pig and being taken and arrested and put in jail.",
      "word_count": 40
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And only due to the fact that my father knew the Polish Commissar for the police, we were released before the Sabbath.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And all these incidents contributed, you know, to my conviction that there was no future for-- for a Jew in Poland.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "All this became much more apparent to me in 1936 when I finished the eighth grade, and I applied to-- to a polytechnic in our town.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "It was a very well-known polytechnical school because it offered courses in-- in textiles and dyeing and also a mechanical department.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And I wanted to go to the mechanical department because I felt that was the only trade that would help me-- that I would be able to contribute something was-- when I get to Israel.",
      "word_count": 35
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And we went through two days of written exams.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And then we were supposed to go to-- for two days of oral exams.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "But because of the excellency of my written exams, my oral exams were waived.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "But when the day came when they announced, you know, who was-- whoa was admitted, my name was called, and I heard the words 'passed, not admitted.' The fact was that only one Jew was admitted to-- to-- to the class.",
      "word_count": 41
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "They practiced in Poland what was known as numerus clausus.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "In-- in schools of-- in middle schools and institutions of higher learning and universities, that meant that only a certain amount of Jews were admitted.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "And, of course, this made very difficult for Jews to-- to-- to acquire an education in Poland.",
      "word_count": 17
    }
  ],
